<h1 id="c:separable-frobenius" class="tex-chapter"><span data-tag="0061">9</span> Separable Frobenius algebras</h1>

<p>
In this chapter, we study duality in the 2-category $\mathbf{Alg}$ of algebras and bimodules, which was introduced in Example&#160;<a href="/tag/004D" data-tag="004D">7.1.2</a>. It turns out that the maximal subcategory with duals in $\mathbf{Alg}$ is the category of separable algebras (which in characteristic zero is the same as finite-dimensional semisimple algebras); if we also want to trivialize the Serre functor (in other words, if we want to have adjunction between evaluation and coevaluation 1-morphisms), we arrive at the notion of a separable symmetric Frobenius algebra. These results will be heavily used later, when we classify extended 2-dimensional TQFTs. 
</p>
<p>
To simplify the exposition, throughout this chapter we assume that $\mathbf{k}$ is a field of characteristic zero. 
</p>
